#if soper
Command provided by: hostserv/onoff
#endif
Help for OFF:

Deactivates the vHost currently assigned to the nick in use.
When you use this command, any user who performs a /whois
on your nick will see your real IP address.

This command will only remain in effect for the duration of
your IRC session, or until you use the ON command.

For permanent removal of your vHost, please use the DISABLE
command.

Syntax: OFF

Examples:
    /msg &nick& OFF
